The paper discusses index structures in storage systems, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also leverages deep-learning models (cs.LG) to improve the performance of index structures. Additionally, the paper proposes a scalable approach (cs.SI) to address the limitations of existing learned index schemes. Finally, the paper uses linear regression models (cs.AI) to construct the learned index.
